36static const decltype(&EVP_hpke_aes_128_gcm) kSupportedAEADs[] = {
37 &EVP_hpke_aes_128_gcm,
38 &EVP_hpke_aes_256_gcm,
39 &EVP_hpke_chacha20_poly1305,
40};
41
42static const EVP_HPKE_AEAD *get_ech_aead(uint16_t aead_id) {
43 for (const auto aead_func : kSupportedAEADs) {
44 const EVP_HPKE_AEAD *aead = aead_func();
45 if (aead_id == EVP_HPKE_AEAD_id(aead)) {
46 return aead;
47 }
48 }
49 return nullptr;
50}
51
52// ssl_client_hello_write_without_extensions serializes |client_hello| into
53// |out|, omitting the length-prefixed extensions. It serializes individual
54// fields, starting with |client_hello->version|, and ignores the
55// |client_hello->client_hello| field. It returns true on success and false on
56// failure.
57static bool ssl_client_hello_write_without_extensions(
58 const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello, CBB *out) {
59 CBB cbb;
60 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, client_hello->version) ||
61 !CBB_add_bytes(out, client_hello->random, client_hello->random_len) ||
62 !CBB_add_u8_length_prefixed(out, &cbb) ||
63 !CBB_add_bytes(&cbb, client_hello->session_id,
64 client_hello->session_id_len) ||
65 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &cbb) ||
66 !CBB_add_bytes(&cbb, client_hello->cipher_suites,
67 client_hello->cipher_suites_len) ||
68 !CBB_add_u8_length_prefixed(out, &cbb) ||
69 !CBB_add_bytes(&cbb, client_hello->compression_methods,
70 client_hello->compression_methods_len) ||
71 !CBB_flush(out)) {
72 return false;
73 }
74 return true;
75}
76
77bool ssl_decode_client_hello_inner(
78 SSL *ssl, uint8_t *out_alert, Array<uint8_t> *out_client_hello_inner,
79 Span<const uint8_t> encoded_client_hello_inner,
80 const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello_outer) {
81 SSL_CLIENT_HELLO client_hello_inner;
82 if (!ssl_client_hello_init(ssl, &client_hello_inner,
83 encoded_client_hello_inner)) {
84 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
85 return false;
86 }
87 // TLS 1.3 ClientHellos must have extensions, and EncodedClientHelloInners use
88 // ClientHelloOuter's session_id.
89 if (client_hello_inner.extensions_len == 0 ||
90 client_hello_inner.session_id_len != 0) {
91 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
92 return false;
93 }
94 client_hello_inner.session_id = client_hello_outer->session_id;
95 client_hello_inner.session_id_len = client_hello_outer->session_id_len;
96
97 // Begin serializing a message containing the ClientHelloInner in |cbb|.
98 ScopedCBB cbb;
99 CBB body, extensions;
100 if (!ssl->method->init_message(ssl, cbb.get(), &body, SSL3_MT_CLIENT_HELLO) ||
101 !ssl_client_hello_write_without_extensions(&client_hello_inner, &body) ||
102 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&body, &extensions)) {
103 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
104 return false;
105 }
106
107 // Sort the extensions in ClientHelloOuter, so ech_outer_extensions may be
108 // processed in O(n*log(n)) time, rather than O(n^2).
109 struct Extension {
110 uint16_t extension = 0;
111 Span<const uint8_t> body;
112 bool copied = false;
113 };
114
115 // MSan's libc interceptors do not handle |bsearch|. See b/182583130.
116 auto compare_extension = [](const void *a, const void *b)
117 NO_SANITIZE_MEMORY -> int {
118 const Extension *extension_a = reinterpret_cast<const Extension *>(a);
119 const Extension *extension_b = reinterpret_cast<const Extension *>(b);
120 if (extension_a->extension < extension_b->extension) {
121 return -1;
122 } else if (extension_a->extension > extension_b->extension) {
123 return 1;
124 }
125 return 0;
126 };
127 GrowableArray<Extension> sorted_extensions;
128 CBS unsorted_extensions(MakeConstSpan(client_hello_outer->extensions,
129 client_hello_outer->extensions_len));
130 while (CBS_len(&unsorted_extensions) > 0) {
131 Extension extension;
132 CBS extension_body;
133 if (!CBS_get_u16(&unsorted_extensions, &extension.extension) ||
134 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&unsorted_extensions, &extension_body)) {
135 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
136 return false;
137 }
138 extension.body = extension_body;
139 if (!sorted_extensions.Push(extension)) {
140 return false;
141 }
142 }
143 qsort(sorted_extensions.data(), sorted_extensions.size(), sizeof(Extension),
144 compare_extension);
145
146 // Copy extensions from |client_hello_inner|, expanding ech_outer_extensions.
147 CBS inner_extensions(MakeConstSpan(client_hello_inner.extensions,
148 client_hello_inner.extensions_len));
149 while (CBS_len(&inner_extensions) > 0) {
150 uint16_t extension_id;
151 CBS extension_body;
152 if (!CBS_get_u16(&inner_extensions, &extension_id) ||
153 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&inner_extensions, &extension_body)) {
154 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
155 return false;
156 }
157 if (extension_id != TLSEXT_TYPE_ech_outer_extensions) {
158 if (!CBB_add_u16(&extensions, extension_id) ||
159 !CBB_add_u16(&extensions, CBS_len(&extension_body)) ||
160 !CBB_add_bytes(&extensions, CBS_data(&extension_body),
161 CBS_len(&extension_body))) {
162 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
163 return false;
164 }
165 continue;
166 }
167
168 // Replace ech_outer_extensions with the corresponding outer extensions.
169 CBS outer_extensions;
170 if (!CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&extension_body, &outer_extensions) ||
171 CBS_len(&extension_body) != 0) {
172 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
173 return false;
174 }
175 while (CBS_len(&outer_extensions) > 0) {
176 uint16_t extension_needed;
177 if (!CBS_get_u16(&outer_extensions, &extension_needed)) {
178 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
179 return false;
180 }
181 if (extension_needed == TLSEXT_TYPE_encrypted_client_hello) {
182 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
183 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
184 return false;
185 }
186 // Find the referenced extension.
187 Extension key;
188 key.extension = extension_needed;
189 Extension *result = reinterpret_cast<Extension *>(
190 bsearch(&key, sorted_extensions.data(), sorted_extensions.size(),
191 sizeof(Extension), compare_extension));
192 if (result == nullptr) {
193 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
194 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
195 return false;
196 }
197
198 // Extensions may be referenced at most once, to bound the result size.
199 if (result->copied) {
200 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
201 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DUPLICATE_EXTENSION);
202 return false;
203 }
204 result->copied = true;
205
206 if (!CBB_add_u16(&extensions, extension_needed) ||
207 !CBB_add_u16(&extensions, result->body.size()) ||
208 !CBB_add_bytes(&extensions, result->body.data(),
209 result->body.size())) {
210 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
211 return false;
212 }
213 }
214 }
215 if (!CBB_flush(&body)) {
216 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
217 return false;
218 }
219
220 // See https://github.com/tlswg/draft-ietf-tls-esni/pull/411
221 CBS extension;
222 if (!ssl_client_hello_init(ssl, &client_hello_inner,
223 MakeConstSpan(CBB_data(&body), CBB_len(&body))) ||
224 !ssl_client_hello_get_extension(&client_hello_inner, &extension,
225 TLSEXT_TYPE_ech_is_inner) ||
226 CBS_len(&extension) != 0 ||
227 ssl_client_hello_get_extension(&client_hello_inner, &extension,
228 TLSEXT_TYPE_encrypted_client_hello) ||
229 !ssl_client_hello_get_extension(&client_hello_inner, &extension,
230 TLSEXT_TYPE_supported_versions)) {
231 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
232 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_INVALID_CLIENT_HELLO_INNER);
233 return false;
234 }
235 // Parse supported_versions and reject TLS versions prior to TLS 1.3. Older
236 // versions are incompatible with ECH.
237 CBS versions;
238 if (!CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&extension, &versions) ||
239 CBS_len(&extension) != 0 || //
240 CBS_len(&versions) == 0) {
241 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
242 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
243 return false;
244 }
245 while (CBS_len(&versions) != 0) {
246 uint16_t version;
247 if (!CBS_get_u16(&versions, &version)) {
248 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
249 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
250 return false;
251 }
252 if (version == SSL3_VERSION || version == TLS1_VERSION ||
253 version == TLS1_1_VERSION || version == TLS1_2_VERSION ||
254 version == DTLS1_VERSION || version == DTLS1_2_VERSION) {
255 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
256 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_INVALID_CLIENT_HELLO_INNER);
257 return false;
258 }
259 }
260
261 if (!ssl->method->finish_message(ssl, cbb.get(), out_client_hello_inner)) {
262 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
263 return false;
264 }
265 return true;
266}
267
268bool ssl_client_hello_decrypt(
269 EVP_HPKE_CTX *hpke_ctx, Array<uint8_t> *out_encoded_client_hello_inner,
270 bool *out_is_decrypt_error, const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello_outer,
271 uint16_t kdf_id, uint16_t aead_id, const uint8_t config_id,
272 Span<const uint8_t> enc, Span<const uint8_t> payload) {
273 *out_is_decrypt_error = false;
274
275 // Compute the ClientHello portion of the ClientHelloOuterAAD value. See
276 // draft-ietf-tls-esni-09, section 5.2.
277 ScopedCBB ch_outer_aad_cbb;
278 CBB enc_cbb, outer_hello_cbb, extensions_cbb;
279 if (!CBB_init(ch_outer_aad_cbb.get(), 0) ||
280 !CBB_add_u16(ch_outer_aad_cbb.get(), kdf_id) ||
281 !CBB_add_u16(ch_outer_aad_cbb.get(), aead_id) ||
282 !CBB_add_u8(ch_outer_aad_cbb.get(), config_id) ||
283 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(ch_outer_aad_cbb.get(), &enc_cbb) ||
284 !CBB_add_bytes(&enc_cbb, enc.data(), enc.size()) ||
285 !CBB_add_u24_length_prefixed(ch_outer_aad_cbb.get(), &outer_hello_cbb) ||
286 !ssl_client_hello_write_without_extensions(client_hello_outer,
287 &outer_hello_cbb) ||
288 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&outer_hello_cbb, &extensions_cbb)) {
289 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
290 return false;
291 }
292
293 CBS extensions(MakeConstSpan(client_hello_outer->extensions,
294 client_hello_outer->extensions_len));
295 while (CBS_len(&extensions) > 0) {
296 uint16_t extension_id;
297 CBS extension_body;
298 if (!CBS_get_u16(&extensions, &extension_id) ||
299 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&extensions, &extension_body)) {
300 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
301 return false;
302 }
303 if (extension_id == TLSEXT_TYPE_encrypted_client_hello) {
304 continue;
305 }
306 if (!CBB_add_u16(&extensions_cbb, extension_id) ||
307 !CBB_add_u16(&extensions_cbb, CBS_len(&extension_body)) ||
308 !CBB_add_bytes(&extensions_cbb, CBS_data(&extension_body),
309 CBS_len(&extension_body))) {
310 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
311 return false;
312 }
313 }
314 if (!CBB_flush(ch_outer_aad_cbb.get())) {
315 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
316 return false;
317 }
318
319 // Attempt to decrypt into |out_encoded_client_hello_inner|.
320 if (!out_encoded_client_hello_inner->Init(payload.size())) {
321 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
322 return false;
323 }
324 size_t encoded_client_hello_inner_len;
325 if (!EVP_HPKE_CTX_open(hpke_ctx, out_encoded_client_hello_inner->data(),
326 &encoded_client_hello_inner_len,
327 out_encoded_client_hello_inner->size(), payload.data(),
328 payload.size(), CBB_data(ch_outer_aad_cbb.get()),
329 CBB_len(ch_outer_aad_cbb.get()))) {
330 *out_is_decrypt_error = true;
331 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECRYPTION_FAILED);
332 return false;
333 }
334 out_encoded_client_hello_inner->Shrink(encoded_client_hello_inner_len);
335 return true;
336}

339bool ECHServerConfig::Init(Span<const uint8_t> ech_config,
340 Span<const uint8_t> private_key,
341 bool is_retry_config) {
342 assert(!initialized_);
343 is_retry_config_ = is_retry_config;
344
345 if (!ech_config_.CopyFrom(ech_config)) {
346 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
347 return false;
348 }
349 // Read from |ech_config_| so we can save Spans with the same lifetime as |this|.
350 CBS reader(ech_config_);
351
352 uint16_t version;
353 if (!CBS_get_u16(&reader, &version)) {
354 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
355 return false;
356 }
357 // Parse the ECHConfig, rejecting all unsupported parameters and extensions.
358 // Unlike most server options, ECH's server configuration is serialized and
359 // configured in both the server and DNS. If the caller configures an
360 // unsupported parameter, this is a deployment error. To catch these errors,
361 // we fail early.
362 if (version != TLSEXT_TYPE_encrypted_client_hello) {
363 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNSUPPORTED_ECH_SERVER_CONFIG);
364 return false;
365 }
366
367 CBS ech_config_contents, public_name, public_key, cipher_suites, extensions;
368 uint16_t kem_id, max_name_len;
369 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&reader, &ech_config_contents) ||
370 !CBS_get_u8(&ech_config_contents, &config_id_) ||
371 !CBS_get_u16(&ech_config_contents, &kem_id) ||
372 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&ech_config_contents, &public_key) ||
373 CBS_len(&public_key) == 0 ||
374 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&ech_config_contents, &cipher_suites) ||
375 CBS_len(&cipher_suites) == 0 ||
376 !CBS_get_u16(&ech_config_contents, &max_name_len) ||
377 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&ech_config_contents, &public_name) ||
378 CBS_len(&public_name) == 0 ||
379 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&ech_config_contents, &extensions) ||
380 CBS_len(&ech_config_contents) != 0 || //
381 CBS_len(&reader) != 0) {
382 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
383 return false;
384 }
385
386 // We do not support any ECHConfig extensions, so |extensions| must be empty.
387 if (CBS_len(&extensions) != 0) {
388 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_ECH_SERVER_CONFIG_UNSUPPORTED_EXTENSION);
389 return false;
390 }
391
392 cipher_suites_ = cipher_suites;
393 while (CBS_len(&cipher_suites) > 0) {
394 uint16_t kdf_id, aead_id;
395 if (!CBS_get_u16(&cipher_suites, &kdf_id) ||
396 !CBS_get_u16(&cipher_suites, &aead_id)) {
397 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
398 return false;
399 }
400 // The server promises to support every option in the ECHConfig, so reject
401 // any unsupported cipher suites.
402 if (kdf_id != EVP_HPKE_HKDF_SHA256 || get_ech_aead(aead_id) == nullptr) {
403 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNSUPPORTED_ECH_SERVER_CONFIG);
404 return false;
405 }
406 }
407
408 // We only support one KEM.
409 if (kem_id != EVP_HPKE_DHKEM_X25519_HKDF_SHA256) {
410 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNSUPPORTED_ECH_SERVER_CONFIG);
411 return false;
412 }
413 if (!EVP_HPKE_KEY_init(key_.get(), EVP_hpke_x25519_hkdf_sha256(),
414 private_key.data(), private_key.size())) {
415 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
416 return false;
417 }
418 // Check the public key in the ECHConfig matches the private key.
419 uint8_t expected_public_key[EVP_HPKE_MAX_PUBLIC_KEY_LENGTH];
420 size_t expected_public_key_len;
421 if (!EVP_HPKE_KEY_public_key(key_.get(), expected_public_key,
422 &expected_public_key_len,
423 sizeof(expected_public_key))) {
424 return false;
425 }
426 if (MakeConstSpan(expected_public_key, expected_public_key_len) !=
427 public_key) {
428 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_ECH_SERVER_CONFIG_AND_PRIVATE_KEY_MISMATCH);
429 return false;
430 }
431
432 initialized_ = true;
433 return true;
434}
435
436bool ECHServerConfig::SetupContext(EVP_HPKE_CTX *ctx, uint16_t kdf_id,
437 uint16_t aead_id,
438 Span<const uint8_t> enc) const {
439 assert(initialized_);
440
441 // Check the cipher suite is supported by this ECHServerConfig.
442 CBS cbs(cipher_suites_);
443 bool cipher_ok = false;
444 while (CBS_len(&cbs) != 0) {
445 uint16_t supported_kdf_id, supported_aead_id;
446 if (!CBS_get_u16(&cbs, &supported_kdf_id) ||
447 !CBS_get_u16(&cbs, &supported_aead_id)) {
448 return false;
449 }
450 if (kdf_id == supported_kdf_id && aead_id == supported_aead_id) {
451 cipher_ok = true;
452 break;
453 }
454 }
455 if (!cipher_ok) {
456 return false;
457 }
458
459 static const uint8_t kInfoLabel[] = "tls ech";
460 ScopedCBB info_cbb;
461 if (!CBB_init(info_cbb.get(), sizeof(kInfoLabel) + ech_config_.size()) ||
462 !CBB_add_bytes(info_cbb.get(), kInfoLabel,
463 sizeof(kInfoLabel) /* includes trailing NUL */) ||
464 !CBB_add_bytes(info_cbb.get(), ech_config_.data(), ech_config_.size())) {
465 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
466 return false;
467 }
468
469 assert(kdf_id == EVP_HPKE_HKDF_SHA256);
470 assert(get_ech_aead(aead_id) != NULL);
471 return EVP_HPKE_CTX_setup_recipient(
472 ctx, key_.get(), EVP_hpke_hkdf_sha256(), get_ech_aead(aead_id), enc.data(),
473 enc.size(), CBB_data(info_cbb.get()), CBB_len(info_cbb.get()));
474}
